Hi you all. {{item:3122}} 
I never post here but I have something to say now. 

I love Leauge of Legends a lot. I have played this game for 8years and I will not stop. My favorite gamemode is just normal summoners rift when I play alone but when I play with my friends there's nothing better than good old 3v3. 
I kid you not, I love 3v3 just as much. Me and my friends always play it around autumn time because the theme is so fitting. I love the variety as well. 
And to see that this gamemode will be gone just like dominion is no more...makes me just really sad. 
This is a fast and nice gamemode and adds variety to the game, leaving me refreshed and wanting to play more of 5v5 and 3v3. It's also a place where I have so much fun with my friends. 

Please do not remove 3v3 Riot Games. 
{{item:3104}} {{item:3070}} 
I never write, I don't complain but now I hope my voice is heard, Save Twisted Treeline! 

Please keep a part of the Leauge of Legends that I love. {{item:3170}}

replies.body:
It's a dead game because they didn't do anything to improve on the game mode. Giving it a normal draft would make it even better and that would take basically no time and money to do that. Instead of working on Twisted Treeline they decide to make TFT a permanent game type. I personally think auto chess sucks ass. It is a boring, minimal interactive game type and will definitely end up dying soon.
What happened to Nexus Blitz? That was a very fun game mode with a bunch of random mini games, and the time it took to complete a game was way shorter than a SR match. Or why not make URF a permanent game type? A large part of the community freaking loves URF. Can't wait in a couple years (if not earlier) when TFT is removed from the game.
